name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.move.thread-count
description: The number of threads used to move files.

name: dfs.namenode.delegation.token.renew-interval
description: The renewal interval for delegation token in milliseconds.

name: ha.failover-controller.graceful-fence.connection.retries
description: FC connection retries for graceful fencing

name: hadoop.security.kms.client.authentication.retry-count
description: Number of time to retry connecting to KMS on authentication failure

name: mapreduce.task.userlog.limit.kb
description: The maximum size of user-logs of each task in KB. 0 disables the cap.

name: hadoop.security.uid.cache.secs
description:
This is the config controlling the validity of the entries in the cache
        containing the userId to userName and groupId to groupName used by
        NativeIO getFstat().

name: dfs.namenode.edekcacheloader.interval.ms
description:
When KeyProvider is configured, the interval time of warming
    up edek cache on NN starts up / becomes active. All edeks will be loaded
    from KMS into provider cache. The edek cache loader will try to warm up the
    cache until succeed or NN leaves active state.
